==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} ''[[envie#Middle English|envie]]'' from {{etyl|fro}} ''[[envie#Old French|envie]]'' from {{etyl|la}} ''[[invidia#Latin|invidia]]'' "envy" from ''[[invidere#Latin|invidere]]'' "to look at with malice" from ''in'' + ''videre'' ("on, upon" + "to look, see"). Displaced native {{enm}} ''[[ande#Middle English|ande, onde]]'' "envy" (from {{ang}} ''[[anda#Old English|anda, onda]]'' "breath, emotion, envy, hatred, grudge, dislike"), {{enm}} ''[[nith#Middle English|nithe, nith]]'' "envy, malice" (from {{ang}} ''[[niþ#Old English|nīþ]]'' "envy, hatred, malice, spite, jealousy").

